  "text": "The data flow traces three layers:\n\n**1. NumPy \u2014 Array Creation & Aggregation:**\n- `multiarray.py` exports the C-level `array()` and `asarray()` from `_multiarray_umath` \u2014 these are the fundamental entry points for creating ndarrays from Python objects/lists.\n- `fromnumeric.py` provides the public aggregation API (`sum`, `mean`, `var`, `std`). These use `_wrapreduction()` which dispatches to either the object's own method or `ufunc.reduce()`. The `__array_function__` protocol in `overrides.py` enables dispatch for non-ndarray inputs (e.g., pandas objects).\n- `_methods.py` contains the actual C-method implementations (`_sum`, `_mean`, `_var`, `_std`) that are called by ndarray methods. These use `umr_sum = um.add.reduce` and `umr_maximum/minimum` for the core computation, and `_count_reduce_items` for element counting.\n\n**2. Pandas \u2014 Array Wrapping/Integration:**\n- `construction.py:array()` is the `pd.array()` factory that creates ExtensionArrays from sequences, using `np.asarray` under the hood for numpy-backed data.\n- `NumpyExtensionArray` in `numpy_.py` wraps a raw `np.ndarray` inside pandas' ExtensionArray interface. Its `__array__()` method (line 153) returns `np.asarray(self._ndarray, dtype=dtype)`, enabling seamless extraction.\n- `generic.py:__array__()` (line 2149, on DataFrame) calls `np.asarray(self._values)` \u2014 this is the protocol that numpy calls when you pass a DataFrame/Series to `np.array()` or `np.asarray()`.\n- `series.py:__array__()` (line 978) similarly converts Series to ndarray, documented as the hook for `numpy.array()` and `numpy.asarray()`.\n\n**3. SciPy \u2014 Statistical Computation:**\n- `_array_api.py:array_namespace()` determines whether inputs are numpy arrays (default) or array-API-compatible, then `_asarray()` provides the SciPy-specific array coercion with `check_finite` support.\n- `_stats_py.py:_chk_asarray()` (line 111) is the universal entry point for stats functions \u2014 calls `xp.asarray(a)` which triggers numpy's `asarray()` which in turn calls `__array__()` on pandas objects.\n- `describe()` (line 1435) chains: `_chk_asarray` \u2192 `xp.mean()` / `_var()` / `skew()` / `kurtosis()`. Each of `_var` and `skew`/`kurtosis` calls `_moment()` which computes central moments via `xp.mean(a, axis=axis)` \u2014 ultimately delegating to numpy's `_mean` in `_methods.py`.\n- `ttest_ind()` (line 6350) uses `array_namespace()` to identify the backend, `xp.asarray()` for type coercion, then computes means/variances of the two samples using numpy aggregation.\n- `_axis_nan_policy.py:_broadcast_arrays()` handles array broadcasting with `xp.asarray()` calls for each input, serving as an intermediary normalization layer before statistical computation.",
